Even at the cost of invading their privacy.
"We try to tell everyone that it is not about spying, but another means of reducing the likelihood of a tragedy," says Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, which is one of the suppliers of surveillance equipment to the Czech market.
"I admit that in some case, such devices may be misused, like when they're put in someone's bag who doesn't know it, but we haven't encountered a case like that yet."
"Most of the time, customers actually buy it for safety reasons," Pilin added.
According to him, the child should always know for what purpose the "box" is for and how it is used in the event of an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bočková points out that if the child does not want to wear anything like this, he will simply get rid of it.
"Even very young children show great creativity in how to deliberately lose some things when they don't want to be under control."
"Large expectations were raised earlier for parents by cell phones, which, however, can be turned off just like these tracking devices," says Bočková.
It is also questionable whether such a device would actually help in the event of an attack.
"As far as the upcoming kidnapping is concerned, the perpetrator will virtually always ensure that the child has no electronics on him to reveal his location."
"Now it's the phone."
"When the tracking devices start to expand, they will also look for them, because their sale will certainly be supported by massive advertising."
"In that case, the criminals will always be one step ahead of the police," the psychologist says.
However, he admits that a similar device can help in the event of a paedophile assault.
According to Robert Čech of RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both cars and people, even if the tracking device is immediately destroyed after the attack is attacked, its presence can help.
The device may be set to be sent to the positioning periodically after a certain period of time."
"If it is damaged, at least the last position of the person concerned will be available."
